---
keywords:
  - "linear"
  - "jira"
  - "saga"
  - "memory bank"
  - "task authority"
match: any
---

Use each system for its own authority boundary.

- Linear is the source of truth for personal project management.
- Jira is the source of truth for work project management.
- saga is only for local agent execution tracking tied to work already defined elsewhere.
- memory bank is for durable project knowledge, decisions, and handoff context.

Do not create a second backlog in saga or memory bank when the parent work belongs in Linear or Jira.
